com.decoded.stereohttp

Class StereoHttpTask<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.decoded.stereohttp.StereoHttpTask<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type to create using the underlying Http Response data (StereoResponse) from a StereoHttpRequest.

    public class StereoHttpTask<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Http Task, which returns a type of type T The Stereo Task attempts to convert the raw result (which is expected to be in JSON format) into the type T, along with any custom encoder or decoders required.

    Usage

       new StereoHttpTask<MyRecordType>(MyRecordType.class, myStereoClient, 2000).execute(RestRequestBuilders...
   .build());
